The Realme 11 series of 5G smartphones are now equipped with some new budget 5G mobile phones. In this article, you’ll get to know more about the new Realme 11x 5G model. The phone is equipped with a Dimensity 6100+ 5G chipset, 5000mAh battery, 64MP camera and more. Specifications are impressive, pricing is competitive, but what’s it like in the real world for Realme 11X 5G?
}}

content4:
{{
<p>
MediaTek’s Dimensity 6100+ 5G SoC is used in Realme 11X 5G. The chipsets use 6nm TSMC technology and have an 8 cores for 64 bits. The chipset will ensure that your mobile device is faster and more efficient. The phone runs on Realme UI 4.0 based on Android v13 user-friendly. There are no lags or crashes when you’re playing games, video editing, viewing social media and watching videos. With 8 GB onboard and up to 8 GB Dynamic RAM, multitasking is easy, as more than 20 apps can run at the same time in the background.
</p>
There is a 5000mAh battery under the hood for Realme 11X 5G. The phone’s battery lasts longer even if you use it for calling, browse social networks, read articles, attend video calls, listen to music, play light games and do some editing. In spite of all this work, the battery was easily able to last a whole day even if switched it on at night. The battery takes about 35 minutes to get half charged.
<p>
}}
